<item>
            <title>[FLINK-4572] Convert to negative in LongValueToIntValue</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-4572</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Gelly drivers expect that scale 32 edges, represented by the lower 32 bits of &lt;tt&gt;long&lt;/tt&gt; values, can be converted to &lt;tt&gt;int&lt;/tt&gt; values. Values between 2^31 and 2^32 - 1 should be converted to negative integers, which is not supported by &lt;tt&gt;MathUtils.checkedDownCast&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13002398">FLINK-4572</key>
            <summary>Convert to negative in LongValueToIntValue</summary>
